This doesn't work, we wan't to know if assignable from one of the values present in the set, it will always be assignable from Connection.
To get the same logic I would need something like this
HashSet<Class<? extends Connection>> includes = new HashSet<>();
HashSet<Class<? extends Connection>> excludes = new HashSet<>();

_set = new IncludeExcludeSet<>(includes, connection ->
{
    if (connection == null)
        return false;
    return includes.stream().anyMatch(c -> c.isAssignableFrom(connection.getClass()));
},
excludes, connection ->
{
    if (connection == null)
        return false;
    return excludes.stream().anyMatch(c -> c.isAssignableFrom(connection.getClass()));
});
so seems easier to just define the set type.
